From: Yue Tao <Yue.Tao@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 19 Nov 2014 14:55:34 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Update the comment of TIPC_UNICLUSTER_FRIENDLY option

The option should be enabled when connecting with TIPC 2.x.

Signed-off-by: Yue Tao <Yue.Tao@windriver.com>
---
 net/tipc/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/tipc/Kconfig b/net/tipc/Kconfig
index 3221c99..cdef83a 100644
--- a/net/tipc/Kconfig
+++ b/net/tipc/Kconfig
@@ -149,7 +149,7 @@ config TIPC_UNICLUSTER_FRIENDLY
 	help
  	  This allows TIPC to communicate with nodes in its cluster that
 	  pre-date the introduction of multi-cluster TIPC support (that is,
-	  nodes running TIPC 1.6 or earlier).
+	  nodes running TIPC 1.6 or earlier, and TIPC 2.x or later).
 
 config TIPC_MULTIPLE_LINKS
 	bool "Enable redundant link support"
